Peru Stocks: Alturas, Buenaventura, Cerro Verde, Relapasa

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-05-18T15:25:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/peru-stocks-alturas-buenaventura-cerro-verde-relapasa.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 10:37 a.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index rose 0.7 percent to 22,119.40. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index increased 1.6 percent to 2,840.77.  Peruvian mining and precious metal stocks gained as
commodity prices increased.  Minas Buenaventura S.A. (BVN PE), Peru’s biggest precious
metals producer, rose 3.1 percent to $41 as gold gained for the
first time in four days in New York as concern about  Europe ’s
debt woes and faster inflation boosted demand for an alternative
investment. Gold for June delivery gained $16.40, or 1.1
percent, to $1,496.40 an ounce on the Comex.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, advanced 5.9 percent to 18 cents. Sociedad
Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan
Copper & Gold Inc., gained 2.4 percent to $43.50. Volcan Cia
Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc producer, climbed
1.8 percent to 3.46 soles as zinc rose 4.1 percent on the London
metal exchange, leading an advance of all six LME metals.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol TPF SA, increased 1.6 percent to 1.93 soles as crude oil
rose from a three-month low. Crude oil for June delivery gained
$2.46, or 2.5 percent, to $99.37 a barrel.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in  New York  at 
